HEADWORD: Gravenstein
<hw>Gra"ven*stein"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called
because it came from Gravenstein, a place in Schleswig.
<au>Downing.</au>]</ety> <def>A kind of fall apple, marked with streaks
of deep red and orange, and of excellent flavor and quality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

